{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1014,"text":"Today, I'm going to talk about AI and us."},{"time":6206,"text":"AI researchers have always said"},{"time":8373,"text":"that we humans do not need to worry,"},{"time":10991,"text":"because only menial jobs\nwill be taken over by machines."},{"time":15274,"text":"Is that really true?"},{"time":18365,"text":"They have also said\nthat AI will create new jobs,"},{"time":22216,"text":"so those who lose their jobs\nwill find a new one."},{"time":26264,"text":"Of course."},{"time":27643,"text":"But the real question is:"},{"time":29839,"text":"How many of those\nwho may lose their jobs to AI"},{"time":33968,"text":"will be able to land a new one,"},{"time":36481,"text":"especially when AI is smart enough\nto learn better than most of us?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":43397,"text":"Let me ask you a question:"},{"time":46666,"text":"How many of you think"},{"time":48488,"text":"that AI will pass the entrance examination\nof a top university by 2020?"},{"time":55836,"text":"Oh, so many. OK."},{"time":58317,"text":"So some of you may say, \"Of course, yes!\""},{"time":63369,"text":"Now singularity is the issue."},{"time":66590,"text":"And some others may say, \"Maybe,"},{"time":69709,"text":"because AI already won\nagainst a top Go player.\""},{"time":75213,"text":"And others may say, \"No, never. Uh-uh.\""},{"time":80195,"text":"That means we do not know\nthe answer yet, right?"},{"time":84268,"text":"So that was the reason why\nI started Todai Robot Project,"},{"time":89252,"text":"making an AI which passes\nthe entrance examination"},{"time":93148,"text":"of the University of Tokyo,"},{"time":95761,"text":"the top university in Japan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99464,"text":"This is our Todai Robot."},{"time":104131,"text":"And, of course, the brain of the robot\nis working in the remote server."},{"time":110747,"text":"It is now writing a 600-word essay"},{"time":114993,"text":"on maritime trade in the 17th century."},{"time":119136,"text":"How does that sound?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":122113,"text":"Why did I take the entrance exam\nas its benchmark?"},{"time":127098,"text":"Because I thought we had to study\nthe performance of AI"},{"time":131863,"text":"in comparison to humans,"},{"time":134001,"text":"especially on the skills and expertise"},{"time":136885,"text":"which are believed\nto be acquired only by humans"},{"time":140997,"text":"and only through education."},{"time":143782,"text":"To enter Todai, the University of Tokyo,"},{"time":147849,"text":"you have to pass\ntwo different types of exams."},{"time":152294,"text":"The first one is\na national standardized test"},{"time":156078,"text":"in multiple-choice style."},{"time":158505,"text":"You have to take seven subjects"},{"time":160984,"text":"and achieve a high score --"},{"time":162963,"text":"I would say like an 85 percent\nor more accuracy rate --"},{"time":167759,"text":"to be allowed to take\nthe second stage written test"},{"time":171870,"text":"prepared by Todai."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174994,"text":"So let me first explain\nhow modern AI works,"},{"time":180335,"text":"taking the \"Jeopardy!\" challenge\nas an example."},{"time":185539,"text":"Here is a typical \"Jeopardy!\" question:"},{"time":188642,"text":"\"Mozart's last symphony\nshares its name with this planet.\""},{"time":194195,"text":"Interestingly, a \"Jeopardy!\"\nquestion always asks,"},{"time":198232,"text":"always ends with \"this\" something:"},{"time":201584,"text":"\"this\" planet, \"this\" country,"},{"time":204435,"text":"\"this\" rock musician, and so on."},{"time":207067,"text":"In other words, \"Jeopardy!\" doesn't ask\nmany different types of questions,"},{"time":211390,"text":"but a single type,"},{"time":213251,"text":"which we call \"factoid questions.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":216975,"text":"By the way, do you know the answer?"},{"time":221980,"text":"If you do not know the answer\nand if you want to know the answer,"},{"time":226059,"text":"what would you do?"},{"time":228160,"text":"You Google, right? Of course."},{"time":231316,"text":"Why not?"},{"time":232820,"text":"But you have to pick appropriate keywords"},{"time":236436,"text":"like \"Mozart,\" \"last\"\nand \"symphony\" to search."},{"time":241462,"text":"The machine basically does the same."},{"time":244457,"text":"Then this Wikipedia page\nwill be ranked top."},{"time":249840,"text":"Then the machine reads the page."},{"time":251772,"text":"No, uh-uh."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253470,"text":"Unfortunately, none of the modern AIs,"},{"time":256956,"text":"including Watson, Siri and Todai Robot,"},{"time":260948,"text":"is able to read."},{"time":263437,"text":"But they are very good\nat searching and optimizing."},{"time":268158,"text":"It will recognize"},{"time":270866,"text":"that the keywords \"Mozart,\"\n\"last\" and \"symphony\""},{"time":273825,"text":"are appearing heavily around here."},{"time":277790,"text":"So if it can find a word which is a planet"},{"time":282189,"text":"and which is co-occurring\nwith these keywords,"},{"time":285861,"text":"that must be the answer."},{"time":288762,"text":"This is how Watson finds\nthe answer \"Jupiter,\" in this case."}]},{"cues":[{"time":296433,"text":"Our Todai Robot works similarly,\nbut a bit smarter"},{"time":300506,"text":"in answering history yes-no questions,"},{"time":304560,"text":"like, \"'Charlemagne repelled the Magyars.'\nIs this sentence true or false?\""},{"time":311181,"text":"Our robot starts producing\na factoid question,"},{"time":315278,"text":"like: \"Charlemagne repelled\n[this person type]\" by itself."},{"time":320995,"text":"Then, \"Avars\" but not\n\"Magyars\" is ranked top."},{"time":326357,"text":"This sentence is likely to be false."},{"time":330772,"text":"Our robot does not read,\ndoes not understand,"},{"time":336335,"text":"but it is statistically\ncorrect in many cases."}]},{"cues":[{"time":342147,"text":"For the second stage written test,"},{"time":344679,"text":"it is required to write\na 600-word essay like this one:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":349809,"text":"[Discuss the rise and fall\nof the maritime trade"},{"time":352111,"text":"in East and Southeast Asia\nin the 17th century ...]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":354557,"text":"and as I have shown earlier,"},{"time":355968,"text":"our robot took the sentences\nfrom the textbooks and Wikipedia,"},{"time":360186,"text":"combined them together,"},{"time":362171,"text":"and optimized it to produce an essay"},{"time":365814,"text":"without understanding a thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":368045,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":369806,"text":"But surprisingly, it wrote a better essay"},{"time":374725,"text":"than most of the students."}]},{"cues":[{"time":376310,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":378725,"text":"How about mathematics?"},{"time":381354,"text":"A fully automatic math-solving machine"},{"time":384536,"text":"has been a dream"},{"time":386191,"text":"since the birth of the word\n\"artificial intelligence,\""},{"time":391785,"text":"but it has stayed at the level\nof arithmetic for a long, long time."},{"time":399530,"text":"Last year, we finally succeeded\nin developing a system"},{"time":404904,"text":"which solved pre-university-level\nproblems from end to end,"},{"time":410101,"text":"like this one."},{"time":413648,"text":"This is the original problem\nwritten in Japanese,"},{"time":417674,"text":"and we had to teach it\n2,000 mathematical axioms"},{"time":422095,"text":"and 8,000 Japanese words"},{"time":424893,"text":"to make it accept the problems\nwritten in natural language."},{"time":430234,"text":"And it is now translating\nthe original problems"},{"time":433800,"text":"into machine-readable formulas."},{"time":438578,"text":"Weird, but it is now ready\nto solve it, I think."},{"time":444701,"text":"Go and solve it."},{"time":446818,"text":"Yes! It is now executing\nsymbolic computation."},{"time":452030,"text":"Even more weird,"},{"time":453634,"text":"but probably this is the most\nfun part for the machine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":458483,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":460858,"text":"Now it outputs a perfect answer,"},{"time":463697,"text":"though its proof is impossible to read,\neven for mathematicians."},{"time":470773,"text":"Anyway, last year our robot\nwas among the top one percent"},{"time":478199,"text":"in the second stage written\nexam in mathematics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":482652,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":486412,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":487747,"text":"So, did it enter Todai?"},{"time":490981,"text":"No, not as I expected."},{"time":494783,"text":"Why?"},{"time":496206,"text":"Because it doesn't understand any meaning."},{"time":500308,"text":"Let me show you a typical error\nit made in the English test."}]},{"cues":[{"time":504411,"text":"[Nate: We're almost at the bookstore.\nJust a few more minutes."},{"time":507412,"text":"Sunil: Wait. ______ .\nNate: Thank you! That always happens ...]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":510475,"text":"Two people are talking."},{"time":511650,"text":"For us, who can understand\nthe situation --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":513704,"text":"[1. \"We walked for a long time.\"\n2. \"We're almost there.\""},{"time":516501,"text":"3. \"Your shoes look expensive.\"\n4. \"Your shoelace is untied.\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":519557,"text":"it is obvious number four\nis the correct answer, right?"},{"time":522454,"text":"But Todai Robot chose number two,"},{"time":524716,"text":"even after learning 15 billion\nEnglish sentences"},{"time":530100,"text":"using deep learning technologies."},{"time":535600,"text":"OK, so now you might\nunderstand what I said:"},{"time":540399,"text":"modern AIs do not read,"},{"time":543071,"text":"do not understand."},{"time":545516,"text":"They only disguise as if they do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":552867,"text":"This is the distribution graph"},{"time":555872,"text":"of half a million students\nwho took the same exam as Todai Robot."},{"time":562558,"text":"Now our Todai Robot\nis among the top 20 percent,"},{"time":568986,"text":"and it was capable to pass"},{"time":571425,"text":"more than 60 percent\nof the universities in Japan --"},{"time":575390,"text":"but not Todai."},{"time":578116,"text":"But see how it is beyond the volume zone"},{"time":582165,"text":"of to-be white-collar workers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":588060,"text":"You might think I was delighted."},{"time":591939,"text":"After all, my robot was surpassing\nstudents everywhere."},{"time":597022,"text":"Instead, I was alarmed."},{"time":601086,"text":"How on earth could this unintelligent\nmachine outperform students --"},{"time":606717,"text":"our children?"},{"time":608033,"text":"Right?"},{"time":610101,"text":"I decided to investigate\nwhat was going on in the human world."},{"time":616542,"text":"I took hundreds of sentences\nfrom high school textbooks"},{"time":621859,"text":"and made easy multiple-choice quizzes,"},{"time":625196,"text":"and asked thousands\nof high school students to answer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":630690,"text":"Here is an example:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":631890,"text":"[Buddhism spread to ... ,\nChristianity to ... and Oceania,"},{"time":634732,"text":"and Islam to ...]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":635907,"text":"Of course, the original problems\nare written in Japanese,"},{"time":638671,"text":"their mother tongue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639850,"text":"[ ______ has spread to Oceania."},{"time":641389,"text":"1. Hinduism 2. Christianity\n3. Islam 4. Buddhism ]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":643830,"text":"Obviously, Christianity\nis the answer, isn't it?"},{"time":646153,"text":"It's written!"},{"time":649482,"text":"And Todai Robot chose\nthe correct answer, too."},{"time":654758,"text":"But one-third of junior\nhigh school students"},{"time":659661,"text":"failed to answer this question."},{"time":664456,"text":"Do you think it is only the case in Japan?"},{"time":667639,"text":"I do not think so,"},{"time":669639,"text":"because Japan is always ranked\namong the top in OECD PISA tests,"},{"time":676034,"text":"measuring 15-year-old\nstudents' performance in mathematics,"},{"time":679985,"text":"science and reading"},{"time":681973,"text":"every three years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":687390,"text":"We have been believing"},{"time":689467,"text":"that everybody can learn"},{"time":691534,"text":"and learn well,"},{"time":693463,"text":"as long as we provide\ngood learning materials"},{"time":697184,"text":"free on the web"},{"time":698663,"text":"so that they can access\nthrough the internet."},{"time":701756,"text":"But such wonderful materials\nmay benefit only those who can read well,"},{"time":708534,"text":"and the percentage\nof those who can read well"},{"time":712493,"text":"may be much less than we expected."},{"time":718040,"text":"How we humans will coexist with AI"},{"time":722305,"text":"is something we have\nto think about carefully,"},{"time":725851,"text":"based on solid evidence."},{"time":729063,"text":"At the same time,\nwe have to think in a hurry"},{"time":733064,"text":"because time is running out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":736106,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":737626,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":742211,"text":"Chris Anderson: Noriko, thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":744315,"text":"Noriko Arai: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":746104,"text":"CA: In your talk, you so beautifully\ngive us a sense of how AIs think,"},{"time":751432,"text":"what they can do amazingly"},{"time":753020,"text":"and what they can't do."},{"time":754739,"text":"But -- do I read you right,"},{"time":756257,"text":"that you think we really need\nquite an urgent revolution in education"},{"time":761551,"text":"to help kids do the things\nthat humans can do better than AIs?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":765730,"text":"NA: Yes, yes, yes."},{"time":767082,"text":"Because we humans\ncan understand the meaning."},{"time":771141,"text":"That is something\nwhich is very, very lacking in AI."},{"time":776071,"text":"But most of the students\njust pack the knowledge"},{"time":780463,"text":"without understanding\nthe meaning of the knowledge,"},{"time":784390,"text":"so that is not knowledge,\nthat is just memorizing,"},{"time":787223,"text":"and AI can do the same thing."},{"time":789697,"text":"So we have to think about\na new type of education."}]},{"cues":[{"time":793352,"text":"CA: A shift from knowledge,\nrote knowledge, to meaning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":796665,"text":"NA: Mm-hmm."}]},{"cues":[{"time":797840,"text":"CA: Well, there's a challenge\nfor the educators. Thank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":801104,"text":"NA: Thank you very much. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":802826,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}